{"at": "2026-05-31T04:43:10Z", "commit_ref": "5858e39", "intent": "spec", "actor": "agent", "kind": "output", "content": "Authored .spec-md from empty for spec 0022 \"Add Optical Constructor\".\n\nSource of truth read: specs/0022/.manual/010-optical-constructor-spec-and-tech-stack.md (the operator's preliminary research / agreed tech stack), plus engine code analysis.\n\nScope decision (recorded in spec A.0): the preliminary research spans 9 feature categories; under this project's minimum-implementation / singular-direction discipline the first spec delivers only the gating foundation, with UI, materials library, optimization/ALGLIB, charts, branch evaluation, lens/curved-mirror physics, and the .binz bulk format explicitly deferred to named later cycles.\n\nSpec shape:\n- Part 0 binding constraints: F#-first net10.0; reuse engine types (IncidentLightInfo, OpticalSystem, Polarization); explicit deferred-scope list; plausible-expansion exclusions (no solver invocation, no engine-type edits, no caching/retry/migration, no new optimization backend).\n- Part A (CRITICAL): beam-tree topology domain model in the existing stub OpticalModel project — ElementId/ElementClass, ElementKind palette DU (LightSource/Polarizer/Sample/Analyzer/Detector/Lens/CurvedMirror), OpticalElement with per-element default LengthUnit/SpectralUnit, recursive BeamTree with reflected/transmitted branches, and a smart constructor enforcing the mirror invariant (mirror => transmitted = None). Reuses engine RT discriminator. Data + total functions only.\n- Part B: canonical JSON persistence — System.Text.Json + FSharp.SystemTextJson + a System.Numerics.Complex converter; save/load with JsonSchema.Net validate-on-load against a shipped schema; canonical extension .ocsys.json cross-checked against root .gitignore (no collision).\n- Part C: add angstrom measure and eV (E=1239.841984/nm) + cm^-1 (1e7/nm) conversions to Constants.fs, additive only; WaveLength DU untouched.\n\nClosing sections: Acceptance criteria (AC-A1..A4, AC-B1..B3, AC-C1), Files in scope (3 new OpticalModel sources + schema + example + fsproj edit; Constants.fs edit; 2 new test files + BerremanTests.fsproj edit), Test artifacts (xUnit v3 + FsCheck + FluentAssertions, all already referenced), References.\n\nAll file:line pointers cited in the spec were verified with the Read tool against the current tree (Media.fs:94, Fields.fs:61/280/314/338, MaterialProperties.fs:59, Solvers.fs:140-147/199, Constants.fs:5-33, MathNetNumericsMath.fs:3-4, OpticalModel/Primitives.fs:1, OpticalModel.fsproj:4, BerremanTests.fsproj:39-51, .gitignore:78/80/209/331). Verified ALGLIB is NOT currently referenced anywhere in the tree, so the research's \"already referenced\" claim was not propagated; ALGLIB is recorded only as a forward decision for the deferred optimization cycle.\n"}
