CustomObject]@{\\n  gatehistory_lines = [IO.File]::ReadAllLines(\\\"$sf\\\\.gate-history\\\").Count\\n  history_lines  ...\nAll artifacts are now verified and consistent. The gate-keeper cycle for spec 0022 is complete.\n\n## Summary\n\nI reconciled `.spec-md` (the Optical Constructor spec — five new F# projects under `Berreman/OpticalConstructor/`: Domain, Storage, Optimization, Ui, App) against the `.gates/` tree and recorded three decisions.\n\n**Decisions (`.gate-history`, 3 rows):**\n\n1. **`include` build** — §A.1 adds the five new projects *to* the existing `Berreman.slnx`, and the `build` gate runs `dotnet build Berreman/Berreman.slnx` with `applies_to: Berreman/**`, so it already compiles all the new code. Reuse rather than add a redundant constructor build gate.\n2. **`include` unit-tests** — the spec reuses the engine unchanged (§A.2–A.3); `BerremanTests` guards against regressions in the solver/field/material types the new projects consume.\n3. **`propose-new` constructor-unit-tests** — nothing currently runs tests over `Berreman/OpticalConstructor/**` (the `unit-tests` gate targets only `BerremanTests`). This directly serves the operator's mandate that functionality be **testable via a UI-less surface first**: §A.6/P3 keeps `model`/`update` free of Avalonia types, so the Domain/Storage/Optimization logic (beam-tree orchestration, units spine, JSON round-trip + schema validation, optimization interface, gradient discretize) is unit-testable headlessly.\n\n**Files written (all within allowed scope):**\n- `.spec-bundle` → `gates: [\"build\", \"unit-tests\"]`\n- `.gate-history` → 3 JSONL decision rows\n- `.proposed-gates/OpticalConstructor/.gates-md` → new group doc (the `Berreman` group is scoped to the pure solver; the constructor app is a distinct subsystem)\n- `.proposed-gates/OpticalConstructor/constructor-unit-tests.gates` → draft `kind: command` descriptor, with one `# TODO(agent-uncertain)` on `command` (the test-project name/path isn't named in the spec; inferred from the `BerremanTests` convention)\n- `.history` → one `decision` line via the safe writer (`history_cli`)\n\n**Note on the run:** the harness delivered tool results out of order and re-ran several calls, which (a) appended ~106 duplicate decision lines to `.history` and (b) left `.gate-history` empty. I cleaned `.history` back to 33 lines (exactly one safe-writer gate decision, all lines valid JSON), rewrote `.gate-history` with the correct 3 rows, and removed the transient content file I'd staged under `.artifacts/`. Final state confirmed: `.gate-history`=3 rows, `.history`=33 lines, bundle gates=`build,unit-tests`, temp file gone.\nAll artifacts are now verified and consistent. The gate-keeper cycle for spec 0022 is complete.\n\n## Summary\n\nI reconciled `.spec-md` (the Optical Constructor spec — five new F# projects under `Berreman/OpticalConstructor/`: Domain, Storage, Optimization, Ui, App) against the `.gates/` tree and recorded three decisions.\n\n**Decisions (`.gate-history`, 3 rows):**\n\n1. **`include` build** — §A.1 adds the five new projects *to* the existing `Berreman.slnx`, and the `build` gate runs `dotnet build Berreman/Berreman.slnx` with `applies_to: Berreman/**`, so it already compiles all the new code. Reuse rather than add a redundant constructor build gate.\n2. **`include` unit-tests** — the spec reuses the engine unchanged (§A.2–A.3); `BerremanTests` guards against regressions in the solver/field/material types the new projects consume.\n3. **`propose-new` constructor-unit-tests** — nothing currently runs tests over `Berreman/OpticalConstructor/**` (the `unit-tests` gate targets only `BerremanTests`). This directly serves the operator's mandate that functionality be **testable via a UI-less surface first**: §A.6/P3 keeps `model`/`update` free of Avalonia types, so the Domain/Storage/Optimization logic (beam-tree orchestration, units spine, JSON round-trip + schema validation, optimization interface, gradient discretize) is unit-testable headlessly.\n\n**Files written (all within allowed scope):**\n- `.spec-bundle` → `gates: [\"build\", \"unit-tests\"]`\n- `.gate-history` → 3 JSONL decision rows\n- `.proposed-gates/OpticalConstructor/.gates-md` → new group doc (the `Berreman` group is scoped to the pure solver; the constructor app is a distinct subsystem)\n- `.proposed-gates/OpticalConstructor/constructor-unit-tests.gates` → draft `kind: command` descriptor, with one `# TODO(agent-uncertain)` on `command` (the test-project name/path isn't named in the spec; inferred from the `BerremanTests` convention)\n- `.history` → one `decision` line via the safe writer (`history_cli`)\n\n**Note on the run:** the harness delivered tool results out of order and re-ran several calls, which (a) appended ~106 duplicate decision lines to `.history` and (b) left `.gate-history` empty. I cleaned `.history` back to 33 lines (exactly one safe-writer gate decision, all lines valid JSON), rewrote `.gate-history` with the correct 3 rows, and removed the transient content file I'd staged under `.artifacts/`. Final state confirmed: `.gate-history`=3 rows, `.history`=33 lines, bundle gates=`build,unit-tests`, temp file gone."}
